{
  "stem": "22237.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We used to play, we never knew a difference.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We knew a difference in so far that we were Jewish, they were Christians.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I remember very well that came-- came Christmas, they would invite me-- my friend would invite me to come to her house, and she would show me the Christmas tree.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And came Hanukkah, she would come to our house, and we would show her the-- the Hanukkah lamp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we would exchange little presents.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And as soon as Hitler came on power, you could feel that-- I could feel that they didn't want to play with me anymore, and that was very hard for a child.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I remember that I took that very serious.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I couldn't even understand in the beginning why my friends avoided me until my parents told me, well, Hitler is on power, and they probably don't want-- their parents probably don't want their children to play with Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So one after the other happened.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My parents had friends, non-Jewish friends, in the building, and you could see that they avoided them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and this is how it started.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then I remember, even back in 1933, the first thing that I really experienced, the-- what the Nazis were up to was, when I went with my mother shopping, and right there, it was getting a little dark, and right in the middle of a shopping area, they-- there was a bonfire, a fire right in the middle of the street.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And people came and held books written by Jewish authors, and they were throwing them in that fire.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had the children with them, and they handed them-- the books to the children.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the children threw the books into that bonfire in the middle of the street.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
